g1601.definition: [ἐκπίπτω] from {{g1537}} and {{g4098}}; to drop away; specially, be driven out of one's course; figuratively, to lose, become inefficient

g1602.definition: [ἐκπλέω] from {{g1537}} and {{g4126}}; to depart by ship

g1605.definition: [ἐκπλήσσω] from {{g1537}} and {{g4141}}; to strike with astonishment

g1607.definition: [ἐκπορεύομαι] from {{g1537}} and {{g4198}}; to depart, be discharged, proceed, project

g1608.definition: [ἐκπορνεύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g4203}}; to be utterly unchaste

g1609.definition: [ἐκπτύω] from {{g1537}} and {{g4429}}; to spit out, i.e. (figuratively) spurn

g1611.definition: [ἔκστασις] from {{g1839}}; a displacement of the mind, i.e. bewilderment, "ecstasy"

g1614.definition: [ἐκτείνω] from {{g1537}} and teino (to stretch); to extend

g1617.definition: [ἐκτενέστερον] neuter of the comparative of {{g1618}}; more intently

g1620.definition: [ἐκτίθημι] from {{g1537}} and {{g5087}}; to expose; figuratively, to declare

g1621.definition: [ἐκτινάσσω] from {{g1537}} and tinasso (to swing); to shake violently

g1622.definition: [ἐκτός] from {{g1537}}; the exterior; figuratively (as a preposition) aside from, besides

g1624.definition: [ἐκτρέπω] from {{g1537}} and the base of {{g5157}}; to deflect, i.e. turn away (literally or figuratively)

g1625.definition: [ἐκτρέφω] from {{g1537}} and {{g5142}}; to rear up to maturity, i.e. (genitive case) to cherish or train

g1626.definition: [ἔκτρωμα] from a comparative of {{g1537}} and τιτρώσκω (to wound); a miscarriage (abortion), i.e. (by analogy) untimely birth

g1627.definition: [ἐκφέρω] from {{g1537}} and {{g5342}}; to bear out (literally or figuratively)

g1630.definition: [ἔκφοβος] from {{g1537}} and {{g5401}}; frightened out of one's wits

g1632.definition: [ἐκχέω] ,     or (by variation)      ἐκχύνωfrom {{g1537}} and χέω (to pour); to pour forth; figuratively, to bestow

g1636.definition: [ἐλαία] feminine of a presumed derivative from an obsolete primary; an olive (the tree or the fruit)

g1637.definition: [ἔλαιον] neuter of the same as {{g1636}}; olive oil

g1638.definition: [ἐλαιών] from {{g1636}}; an olive-orchard, i.e. (specially) the Mount of Olives

g1639.definition: [Ἐλαμίτης] of Hebrew origin ({{h5867}}); an Elamite or Persian

g1640.definition: [ἐλάσσων]   or ἐλάττωνcomparative of the same as {{g1646}}; smaller (in size, quantity, age or quality)

g1641.definition: [ἐλαττονέω] from {{g1640}}; to diminish, i.e. fall short

g1642.definition: [ἐλαττόω] from {{g1640}}; to lessen (in rank or influence)

g1643.definition: [ἐλαύνω] a prolonged form of a primary verb (obsolete except in certain tenses as an alternative of this) of uncertain affinity; to push (as wind, oars or dæmonical power)

g1645.definition: [ἐλαφρός] probably akin to {{g1643}} and the base of {{g1640}}; light, i.e. easy

g1646.definition: [ἐλάχιστος] superlative of ἔλαχυς (short); used as equivalent to {{g3398}}; least (in size, amount, dignity, etc.)

g1648.definition: [Ἐλεάζαρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h499}}); Eleazar, an Israelite

g1651.definition: [ἐλέγχω] of uncertain affinity; to confute, admonish

g1653.definition: [ἐλεέω] from {{g1656}}; to compassionate (by word or deed, specially, by divine grace)

g1654.definition: [ἐλεημοσύνη] from {{g1656}}; compassionateness, i.e. (as exercised towards the poor) beneficence, or (concretely) a benefaction

g1656.definition: [ἔλεος] of uncertain affinity; compassion (human or divine, especially active)

g1657.definition: [ἐλευθερία] from {{g1658}}; freedom (legitimate or licentious, chiefly moral or ceremonial)

g1658.definition: [ἐλεύθερος] probably from the alternate of {{g2064}}; unrestrained (to go at pleasure), i.e. (as a citizen) not a slave (whether freeborn or manumitted), or (genitive case) exempt (from obligation or liability)

g1659.definition: [ἐλευθερόω] from {{g1658}}; to liberate, i.e. (figuratively) to exempt (from moral, ceremonial or mortal liability)

g1660.definition: [ἔλευσις] from the alternate of {{g2064}}; an advent

g1661.definition: [ἐλεφάντινος] from ἔλεφας (an "elephant"); elephantine, i.e. (by implication) composed of ivory

g1662.definition: [Ἐλιακείμ] of Hebrew origin ({{h471}}); Eliakim, an Israelite

g1663.definition: [Ἐλιέζερ] of Hebrew origin ({{h461}}); Eliezer, an Israelite

g1664.definition: [Ἐλιούδ] of Hebrew origin ({{h410}} and {{h1935}}); God of majesty; Eliud, an Israelite

g1665.definition: [Ἐλισάβετ] of Hebrew origin ({{h472}}); Elisabet, an Israelitess

g1666.definition: [Ἐλισσαῖος] of Hebrew origin ({{h477}}); Elissæus, an Israelite

g1667.definition: [ἑλίσσω] a form of {{g1507}}; to coil or wrap

g1668.definition: [ἕλκος] probably from {{g1670}}; an ulcer (as if drawn together)

g1669.definition: [ἑλκόω] from {{g1668}}; to cause to ulcerate, i.e. (passively) be ulcerous

g1670.definition: [ἑλκύω]   or ἕλκω;  probably akin to {{g138}}; to drag (literally or figuratively) Compare {{g1667}}.

g1671.definition: [Ἑλλάς] of uncertain affinity; Hellas (or Greece), a country of Europe

g1672.definition: [Ἕλλην] from {{g1671}}; a Hellen (Grecian) or inhabitant of Hellas; by extension a Greek-speaking person, especially a non-Jew

g1674.definition: [Ἑλληνίς] feminine of {{g1672}}; a Grecian (i.e. non-Jewish) woman

g1675.definition: [Ἑλληνιστής] from a derivative of {{g1672}}; a Hellenist or Greek-speaking Jew

g1676.definition: [Ἑλληνιστί] adverb from the same as {{g1675}}; Hellenistically, i.e. in the Grecian language

g1677.definition: [ἐλλογέω] from {{g1722}} and {{g3056}} (in the sense of account); to reckon in, i.e. attribute

g1678.definition: [Ἐλμωδάμ] of Hebrew origin (perhaps for {{h486}}); Elmodam, an Israelite

g1680.definition: [ἐλπίς] from a primary ἔλπω (to anticipate, usually with pleasure); expectation (abstractly or concretely) or confidence

g1681.definition: [Ἐλύμας] of foreign origin; Elymas, a wizard

g1682.definition: [ἐλοΐ] of Chaldean origin ({{h426}} with pronominal suffix) my God

g1683.definition: [ἐμαυτοῦ] genitive case compound of {{g1700}} and {{g846}}; of myself so likewise the dative case      ἐμαυτῷ, and accusative case      ἐμαυτόν

g1684.definition: [ἐμβαίνω] from {{g1722}} and the base of {{g939}}; to walk on, i.e. embark (aboard a vessel), reach (a pool)

g1685.definition: [ἐμβάλλω] from {{g1722}} and {{g906}}; to throw on, i.e. (figuratively) subject to (eternal punishment)

g1686.definition: [ἐμβάπτω] from {{g1722}} and {{g911}}; to whelm on, i.e. wet (a part of the person, etc.) by contact with a fluid

g1687.definition: [ἐμβατεύω] from {{g1722}} and a presumed derivative of the base of {{g939}}; equivalent to {{g1684}}; to intrude on (figuratively)

g1688.definition: [ἐμβιβάζω] from {{g1722}} and βιβάζω (to mount; causative of {{g1684}}); to place on, i.e. transfer (aboard a vessel)

g1689.definition: [ἐμβλέπω] from {{g1722}} and {{g991}}; to look on, i.e. (relatively) to observe fixedly, or (absolutely) to discern clearly

g1690.definition: [ἐμβριμάομαι] from {{g1722}} and βριμάομαι (to snort with anger); to have indignation on, i.e. (transitively) to blame, (intransitively) to sigh with chagrin, (specially) to sternly enjoin

g1693.definition: [ἐμμαίνομαι] from {{g1722}} and {{g3105}}; to rave on, i.e. rage at

g1694.definition: [Ἐμμανουήλ] of Hebrew origin ({{h6005}}); God with us; Emmanuel, a name of Christ

g1695.definition: [Ἐμμαούς] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{h3222}}); Emmaus, a place in Palestine

g1696.definition: [ἐμμένω] from {{g1722}} and {{g3306}}; to stay in the same place, i.e. (figuratively) persevere

g1697.definition: [Ἐμμόρ] of Hebrew origin ({{h2544}}); Emmor (i.e. Chamor), a Canaanite

g1698.definition: [ἐμοί] a prolonged form of {{g3427}}; to me

g1699.definition: [ἐμός] from the oblique cases of {{g1473}} ({{g1698}}, {{g1700}}, {{g1691}}); my

g1700.definition: [ἐμοῦ] a prolonged form of {{g3449}}; of me
